# Coveo Platform — Pokemon Challenge Context

## Challenge Goal
Build a Coveo-powered search page that indexes **pokemondb.net** and displays Pokemon with:
- Facet filter by **Pokemon Type**
- Facet filter by **Pokemon Generation**
- Pokemon **picture displayed** directly in search results

Stack: **@coveo/headless** + **React** (TypeScript)

---

## Key Platform Concepts

### Organization & Auth
- **Organization ID**: unique identifier for your Coveo org (e.g. `mycoveoorganizationa1b23c`)
- **API Key**: for local dev, use an Anonymous search template API key. Never expose keys tagged "Must remain private"
- **Search Token**: server-generated token preferred for production; use API key for local dev

### Sources
- **Web Crawler source**: crawls URLs automatically. Use URL rules to include only Pokemon pages (`/pokedex/` path) and exclude Moves, Types, Items, etc.
- **Push source**: programmatic push via Push API. Alternative if web crawler cannot isolate the right pages.
- **Tip from challenge**: create a single-pokemon source for fast iteration during development

### Web Scraping Configuration
- JSON config attached to a web source that controls what content is extracted
- Use it to extract specific metadata fields (type, generation, image URL) from HTML elements
- CSS selectors target the exact table cells / elements you want
- Attach it in the Coveo Admin Console under Sources → your source → Web Scraping Config

### Fields
- Coveo auto-maps metadata to fields with matching names
- Custom fields must be created in Admin Console → Content → Fields BEFORE they show up in facets
- Relevant custom fields to create for this project:
  - `pokemontype` (multi-value, string) — Pokemon element type(s)
  - `pokemongeneration` (string) — Generation number/name
  - `pictureuri` (string) — URL of Pokemon's official sprite/image
- Default fields: `title`, `uri`, `date`, `filetype`, `language` (auto-populated)

### Facets
- Facets filter results by field values
- Field must exist in the index AND be marked **Facet: true** in Admin Console → Fields

### Search API
- Endpoint: `https://platform.cloud.coveo.com/rest/search/v2` (US)
- All queries go through a **Query Pipeline** which can apply ranking rules, stop words, etc.

---

## Coveo Admin Console URLs
- Main: https://platform.cloud.coveo.com/admin/
- Sources: `#/orgid/content/sources/`
- Fields: `#/orgid/content/fields/`
- Content Browser (inspect indexed items): `#/orgid/content/browser/`
- Search Pages (built-in editor): `#/orgid/search/pages/`

---

## pokemondb.net Structure
- Individual Pokemon pages: `https://pokemondb.net/pokedex/{name}` — INCLUDE these
- Exclude: `/move/`, `/type/`, `/ability/`, `/item/`, `/mechanic/`, `/pokebase/`, `/evolution/`
- Pokemon image: found in `<div class="infocard-lg">` or the main `<img>` in the Pokedex entry table
- Pokemon type(s): in the table row labeled "Type"
- Pokemon generation: in the table row labeled "Generation"

---

## NPM Packages
- `@coveo/headless` — state management, engine, controllers (pinned to `3.50.1`)
- No separate React wrapper needed for client-side rendering; use vanilla headless with React hooks
